<section class="infra-section">
  <div class="container-lg">
    <div class="infra-editorial">
      <div class="fade-up">
        <span class="infra-kicker">Rudrapur Plant</span>
        <h2 class="infra-title elicyon">Built for volume, consistency, and in-house control.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-up" data-delay="140">
        <p class="infra-copy">
          The manufacturing plant is spread across 1 million sq ft at SIDCUL Pantnagar, Rudrapur in Uttarakhand. The location supports a complete production ecosystem for modern home decor and interior surface products.
        </p>
        <p class="infra-copy">
          Production is supported by German, Korean, and Taiwanese machinery including calendar lines, extrusion machines, laminators, fabric preparation, coating systems, printing and wrapping lines, utility plants, and in-house packaging material capability.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="infra-stats">
      <div class="infra-stat fade-up">
        <strong><span class="odometer" data-odometer-final="1">0</span><span class="infra-stat__suffix">M</span></strong>
        <span>sq ft manufacturing footprint at SIDCUL Pantnagar, Rudrapur</span>
      </div>
      <div class="infra-stat fade-up" data-delay="100">
        <strong><span class="odometer" data-odometer-final="6">0</span></strong>
        <span>German and Korean calendar machines from 2M to 5M width</span>
      </div>
      <div class="infra-stat fade-up" data-delay="200">
        <strong><span class="odometer" data-odometer-final="4000">0</span></strong>
        <span>MT annual PVC foam board capacity from 6 extrusion machines</span>
      </div>
      <div class="infra-stat fade-up" data-delay="300">
        <strong><span class="odometer" data-odometer-final="28">0</span></strong>
        <span>knitting and warping fabric machines for in-house fabric</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

